QueryText: 1.	What is the nutrient requirement for sugarcane?
KCCAns: An average crop of sugarcane yielding 100 t/ha removes 208kg of N, 53kg of P, 280kg of K, 30 kg of Sulphur, 3.4kg of iron, 1.2 kg of manganese, 0.6 kg of copper respectively from the soil. Hence, soil has to be replenished to maintain the productivity of sugarcane with the said quantities of nutrients.
